          "body": "Verse 53 states the Levites' purpose with unusual directness: their encampment around the tabernacle exists 'so that there will be no wrath on the congregation of the sons of Israel.' The word *qetseph* — the burning anger of God — is not a theoretical possibility. It will erupt at Korah's rebellion (Numbers 16:46), at the bronze serpent incident (Numbers 21:6), and at Baal-Peor (Numbers 25:3). The Levitical buffer is not a symbolic gesture; it is a structural provision for the protection of a people who live in the dangerous proximity of a holy God. Calvin observed that God's concession of graded access to His presence — Levites closer, tribes further, priests closest, high priest alone on Yom Kippur — is an act of mercy, not exclusion. The alternative to structured mediation is not free access; it is death (cf. Exodus 19:12-13, 21-24; 2 Samuel 6:6-7)."
